 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/udalynia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dalynia</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amiable Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(3/26/02 8:15:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1456.topic&index=44>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://circe.inetdb.com/~dalynia/images/dalynia-portrait.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: `</span><hr size=1> He means that as long as he is in the aggro radius of a mob (regardless of being KOS or not, or having drawn aggro), he can press 'H' with that mob targetted and get &quot;Hail, Foo Mob.&quot; and not just &quot;Hail.&quot;  This will hold true despite any intervening objects, terrain, doors, other mobs, players, what have you.<br>
<br>
That being said, I don't know what determines the range at which you can be from a targetted mob and get their name when you Hail them.  I don't know if it's aggro range based (seems to be much larger than that) or if it's simply some fixed range from your position. <p>Dalynia Aziz<br>
Arch Mage of Amici<br>
Innoruuk Server<br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=28865"><i>profile</i></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uneochosen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Neochosen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Indifferent Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(3/26/02 8:36:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1456.topic&index=46>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.eqitems.com/tolstoy/aoshi.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: `</span><hr size=1> This does not hold true around walls Daly.  Take Ssra for example, right when you zone in there is a corner and then a door straight ahead.  If someone is fighting a mob just within the door and you are standing on the other side of the corner not only would you get the &quot;You cannot hit your target from here&quot; message, but you will also not be able to Hail the mob, even though if the wall was removed you would be able both melee and hail the mob.  Anyone who fights in Ssra would realize that mobs there have an extremely large melee range (bounding box), and that were the wall removed you would be within melee range of said mob, therefore, the problem is not that you must be standing on top of the mob to hit it (this holds true for other zones).  I can't count the number of times that when we were fighting in the old NToV safe spot I would run around the corner for a heal, yet still be well within what would normally be melee range, be facing the direction of the mob, and yet not be able to hit it nor hail it.<br>
<br>
(editted to make sure it was understood who I was addressing) <p><font face="Monotype Corsiva" size="4" color="#800000"><b><i>Tolstoy Wyldefyre</i></b></font><BR><font face="Bookman Old Style" size="2"><b>Wood Elf Warlord of Innoruuk</b></font><br><a href="http://legionsofdarkness.org"><font face="Bookman Old Style" size="2"><b>Legions of Darkness</b></font></a><br></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uneochosen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Neochosen</A> at: 3/26/02 8:38:45 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ugartegilsson.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gart Egilsson</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Indifferent Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(3/26/02 9:30:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1456.topic&index=47>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://pantheon.yale.edu/~bdiebold/images/Gart1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: `</span><hr size=1> <br>
<br>
<br>
I'm a little lost too Tolstoy.<br>
<br>
If you fight inside door and someone opens the door Zemm and friends come in.  I've seen it, and died from it.  Including two night ago.  <br>
<br>
If you fight inside the door, and no one opens the door, Zemm and friends don't come in.<br>
<br>
What am I missing?   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/urykarderashken.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rykar Derashken</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amiable Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(3/26/02 9:58:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1456.topic&index=49>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   For you uninformed</span><hr size=1> Outdoor zones typically have no solid geometry keeping you from being able to hail a mob from literally anywhere within casting distance.  Even if you have 3 walls in between you and the mob, if your close enough and your in an outdoor zone you can hail him.  <br>
<br>
Now to be able to actually cast a spell on him is another matter as that requires line of sight typically.  Line of sight in EQ is typically determined by being able to &quot;hail&quot; a mob while facing it.  <br>
<br>
Now hailing a mob means you have clear line of sight to its geometric center.  But that doesn't mean you can hit it.  (e.g. Attempting to harmonize black reavers in Rak reaver room from the bottom of the room.  You can hail it but you can't harmonize because you are not really in line of sight and are too high/low to cast on it (&quot;You cannot see your target&quot;) which it doesn't say.<br>
<br>
Now back on topic, outdoor zones typically do not consider any wall/door as a solid obstacle and ignore them when casting spells on mobs.  (e.g. you target a mob in the giant fort in Dreadlands, go around the walls to where mob will not path through other giants and pull with a spell)  There are exceptions to this case.<br>
<br>
In indoor and dungeon zones, doors and other obstacles are almost always considered solid objects which you cannot cast through.  There are of course exceptions to this rule which supports Toystory's theory of invisible doors (e.g. the door in front of the Golem Master spawn point in NWing of Charassis).  I can cast through that door like it wasnt there to pull the mobs.  Perhaps doors aren't all made the same and that some of them DO in fact block the range of assist aggro from the drakes outside HoT.  I know doors INSIDE HoT do not block the assist aggro if a roamer is right behind it and were engaged on a mob.<br>
<br>
But I digress, hailing a mob doesn't necessarily mean it will aggro through a door when you engage another mob near said door. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=19830"><img border=0 src="http://rykar.home.mindspring.com/rypic2002.jpg"></A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uneochosen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Neochosen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Indifferent Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(3/26/02 10:09:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1456.topic&index=50>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.eqitems.com/tolstoy/aoshi.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: For you uninformed</span><hr size=1> Actually, I knew someone was going to bring up that point Rykar.  You're right in that walls in outdoor zones (ex: inn's in WC) and some indoor zones (ex: walls in the bazaar/thurg) are transparent and you can hail mobs through them.  This is due to the fact they aren't part of the &quot;zone wall&quot; geometry.  Only objects that are part of the zone wall gemetry can block casting/hail/ae dmg (ex: The afore mentioned wall in Ssra).  Probally the easiest way to see if a wall is a zone wall is if you can sit/look through it and see no world beyond (ex: sitting the wall at zone in to Sirens).<br>
<br>
This can be tested by sitting just outside the HoT door while an ae'ing wurm was inc and getting hit by the AE (I know several people who have done this and it was part of what led to this (and it has been stated several times in this thread), though I was too busy myself to do so). <p><font face="Monotype Corsiva" size="4" color="#800000"><b><i>Tolstoy Wyldefyre</i></b></font><BR><font face="Bookman Old Style" size="2"><b>Wood Elf Warlord of Innoruuk</b></font><br><a href="http://legionsofdarkness.org"><font face="Bookman Old Style" size="2"><b>Legions of Darkness</b></font></a><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uhalbred2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>halbred2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(3/26/02 10:40:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1456.topic&index=51>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: For you uninformed</span><hr size=1> Why are you so determined to be right Tolstoy ?<br>
Everyone who has been in HoT can by self sight and self pain sign the fact that if you open the door, CoV mobs outside will agro fighting in door area no matter if its in LoS or not....?<br>
And when the door is closed they wont agro.<br>
Why do you insist of doubting something that so many people tell you is a fact and has caused them numerous deaths ?<br>
Screw science, I go for personal experience and if you want to die trying to proof science when its wrong then be my guest...<br>
